      "url": "https://www.citivelocity.com/cvr/retail/eppublic/pb/index.html?platformId=79&ancestor=CVR22",
      "text_preview": "Research\n|\nWeek of Jun 8\nGlobal FX Strategy: Our Risk Sentiment Goes From Yellow to Red\nIn the last week our risk sentiment has moved from green to yellow and now to red. While we still see a positive trend for risk assets, multiple catalysts at play would likely lead to risk-off with higher yields; historically, that's a USD-positive backdrop. We consider strategies herein.\nRead More\nWill the Tech-Led Correction in Japanese Equities Drag On?\nJapanese high-tech stocks had been driving the market since April but have now seen a significant correction, resulting in sharp declines in both the Nikkei and TOPIX. But we see four reasons to think this tech-led correction will likely be short-lived, with significant upside still ahead.\nRead More\nMetal Matters: Why This May Not Be the Gold Dip to Buy\nGold recently closed below its 200dMA for the first time since September 2023. We lower our 0-3-month point-price target to $4,000 an ounce from $4,300. While we maintain a bullish longer-term view"
    }
